def: Coma with complete insensibility; deep lethargy.
To blow, wipe, or clear, as the nose.
The middle space or region between heaven and hell; the abodeof human beings; the earth.
A brush of twigs for sweeping; a broom; anything which sweepsaway or destroys. [Archaic or Fig.]I will sweep it with the besom of destruction. Isa. xiv. 23.The housemaid with her besom. W. Irving.
Enduring through a long time; chronic.
